But hours after his court appearance, Morrison uploaded an image on the social media site wearing the kit of the Hammers London rivals seating in the driver’s seat of a Ferrari sports car.

Morrison, who joined West Ham from Manchester United for £650,000 in January 2012, has admitted before that he is a Gunners supporter and is understood to have followed the club since childhood.

But with his future at Upton Park uncertain, Hammers fans are unlikely to favour his choice of clothing ahead of the start of the new season.

The Hammers face Arsenal later this season on December 28. But Morrison, who underwent minor groin surgery last month, is unlikely to feature at all in West Ham’s first Premier League match of the season is against Tottenham on August 16.

